  "mergedContent": "Adult Companion mare, brilliant white coat, silver hooves, sapphire eyes, silver-white mane; unpartnered for three years before Choosing. Drew toward devastation by the Call; found Rance collapsed in crater surrounded by wild magic residue; recognized Gift-shock and uncontrolled awakening. Chose him despite his age, bitterness, and catastrophic first manifestation—'There is only the right Chosen for each Companion.' Bond formed when eyes locked—mindvoice 'clear as crystal bells, warm as summer sunshine'; poured unconditional love into him, stabilized his fracturing mind with mental bridges across burned channels; revealed he caused the destruction himself. Reciprocal affection now established. Suspects Rance's Gift is rarer/more dangerous than Firestarting; unprecedented in five centuries with no one capable of training it. Promised to incapacitate him if he loses control. STANCE-Rance: Protective, devoted, occasionally frustrated by stubbornness (nipped shoulder for attention, insulted when called 'horse'); accepts his determination; shares his purpose to warn Haven. Confirms Karsite blood magic historically real, officially banned for decades—revival concerning. Rode relentlessly four days/nights without true rest to reach Haven. Met Rolan (Queen's Own Companion) upon arrival; refused to leave Rance's side despite exhaustion. Abilities: Mind-speech with Chosen; can travel three times distance of ordinary horses; heightened magical senses.",
